The Lotus
In the pale mist of dawn,
The sun unfolds its petals;
The day breaks, bright and quiet—
The light is everywhere, a gentle bomb;
The green wide world awakens, the flower.—
Blooms’ fair frame the soft, pale winding breeze.

- Ezra Pound
